latestIgtvVideos.title: Unconditional love
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Part 2 of 2

For both of them, this was a very emotional moment. It was like a reunion of two brothers miles away from their motherland. They didn't have money or job or any sight of a secured future but they had each other's friendship which was their biggest possession

My mother's uncle brought Khanna mama home. My grandmother says, 'The first time Khanna came to our house, he touched my feet and called me didi. From that moment until his death, he truly respected, treated & considered me like his elder sister. And I also loved him like my son. My brother eventually moved back to Calcutta with a job and Khanna found a job in Delhi, not very far from our house. But he never distanced himself from us. His routine was fixed. During his lunch break, he would come home, have a stomach full of rice & fish and rush back to the office. From his first salary, he bought  me a cotton saree and a shirt piece for your grandfather. When I scolded him for this unnecessary expense, he said this is the least a son can do for his maa. He didn't have any family in Delhi so his wedding happened at our house in Hamilton Road. He said you are my maa so you need to welcome your bride. Such was his regard for me. Not once did he miss Bhai Fota(Bhai dooj) in these many years, except the last few, despite his ill health. Few relations are thicker than blood. My relation with Khanna mama was truly a testimony of that. He was godsend.

In today's time, when relationships are based on materialistic accomplishments and wealth, losing people who have nurtured you with unconditional love is truly painful.  Rest in peace, Khanna mama. They don't make men like you anymore. Thank you for the love & values. Thank you

A night to remember ♥️

Surrounded by the roar of legends and the glow of Ferrari red, I had the privilege of attending the India debut of the Ferrari 12Cilindri, a grand tourer that redefines power, design, and Italian craftsmanship.

This wasn’t just a launch; it was a statement. A rare union of art and engineering, where every curve whispered performance and every detail screamed legacy.

I chose a bold yet comfortable look for this milestone moment: a vibrant yellow linen jacket paired with an easy shirt dress and classic trousers, all sourced from @philocaly_menswear. Styled for ease, made for a night that felt like cinema.

Thank you @avanticachaudhry @ferrarinewdelhi for this truly iconic evening. Here’s to more nights that make our hearts race.

An unforgettable afternoon at the Aditya Birla Polo Cup - where tradition met thrill, and every moment echoed with the rhythm of galloping hooves and champagne toasts. 

For an event so timeless, my look had to embody equal parts elegance and ease. Enter @hackettlondon , a name that effortlessly stitches together British heritage with modern flair. I wore a finely crafted polo shirt - soft against the skin yet structured enough to hold its shape, the very definition of comfort meeting form. Paired with lightweight, tailored trousers, it was a masterclass in summer dressing - breezy, breathable, and subtly bold.

As the sun played hide and seek through the trees, the ensemble proved its merit - stylish enough for the stands, relaxed enough for conversation, and functional enough to walk the greens with confidence. Hackett’s sartorial language speaks in modern cuts, fine tailoring, and that distinct British twist — a wardrobe essential that belongs in every gentleman’s collection.

Here’s to afternoons steeped in heritage, impeccable tailoring, and the quiet joy of dressing well — no matter where the day takes you.

#HackettLondon #PoloCupStyle #AdityaBirlaPoloCup #ModernClassic #BritishElegance #MenswearDiaries #LuxuryStyle

Just checked into @theleelaambiencedelhi Delhi, and I’m already in awe! ⭐️♥️

From the warm welcome drink to the breathtaking views from my room, every detail exudes luxury and comfort. The modern amenities, including a deep soaking bathtub, plush bedding, and a well-equipped workspace, make it a perfect blend of relaxation and productivity.

Before indulging in the inviting bathtub, I decided to explore the hotel’s offerings. Café Knosh offers delightful international cuisine by the poolside, while Dilli 32 serves exquisite Indian dishes with a live kitchen experience. For a relaxed evening, Cherry Bar and Club Cuba provide the perfect ambiance with their curated cocktails and live music. ￼ ￼
The spa is a sanctuary of wellness, offering therapies rooted in ancient traditions and modern techniques. The two outdoor swimming pools are perfect for a refreshing dip or lounging under the sun. As one of East Delhi’s premier destinations, the hotel boasts a 25,000 sq.ft. pillarless ballroom, making it ideal for grand events and conventions. ￼

Every corner of this hotel speaks of elegance and impeccable hospitality. Truly, The Leela Ambience Convention Hotel is a gem in the heart of Delhi.

#TheLeelaAmbience #LuxuryStay #DelhiDiaries #theprimeaddressofeastdelhi

latestPosts.caption:
Three days of culture, nature, and unforgettable experiences at the @maharashtraecoglampingfest 

Nestled by the serene Gangapur Dam backwaters in Nasik, this incredible journey with @maharashtratourismofficial gave us a closer look at the state’s rich heritage.

From a Warli art workshop to mesmerizing folk performances, spiritual moments at Trimbakeshwar Temple and Godavari Kund, to sipping wine at Sula Vineyards - every moment was a discovery. The Nasik Heritage Walk was a step back in time, and the Godavari Aarti was pure magic. We wrapped it up with an authentic Maharashtrian farm-to-table feast and some fun cultural activities.

Grateful for this immersive experience! Can’t wait to explore more of #Maharashtra! ❤️

#EcoGlampingFestival #MaharashtraTourism #DiscoverNasik #TravelDiaries #CultureAndTradition #GlampingExperience #SulaVineyards #GodavariAarti #WarliArt #NasikDiaries
